      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load compared between FEA ensemble and experimental measurements using mean error, 95% prediction interval, and Bland-Altman analysis. Mean stiffness error 4.2% (±6.1%); mean yield load error 3.8% (±7.4%). Metrics satisfy acceptance criteria established a priori."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load under ASTM F1717 compression-bending are the regulatory quantities of interest for 510(k) submission. These QoIs directly inform the clinical question of mechanical adequacy under physiologic loading. Linkage to patient risk documented in the risk analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
